			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=1696473&amp;sid=32f634186e869c535397d6396fbe3059#p1696473"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=28806&amp;sid=32f634186e869c535397d6396fbe3059">bertilak</a></strong> &raquo; Wed May 15, 2013 4:29 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content"><blockquote><div><cite>Abe wrote:</cite>If you wait until the end to bid, the other bidders don't have time to find out what your high bid is.</div></blockquote><br />The essence of the thing in a nutshell.<br /><br />A sniping service makes this a snap. You don't even need to be there to make that last second bid, and a perfectly timed one at that.</div>

